{"data":{"acceptance_tests":["test_csv_export.py"],"actor":"M","assignee":"Ravi","bounty":3.0,"brief":"Create a new self-contained module csv_export.py with a function to_csv(summary: dict) -> str. The input 'summary' has the shape produced by report.summarize(): {'total_cost': float, 'by_agent': {agent_name: cost_float, ...}, 'count': int}. Output a CSV-formatted string with a header row 'agent,cost' followed by one row per agent in by_agent (sorted alphabetically by agent name), then a final row 'TOTAL,<total_cost>'. Format all cost floats with exactly 2 decimal places (e.g. '1.50'). Use '\\n' as line separator, and end the string with a trailing newline. Do NOT import from report.py or any other task dir - just accept the dict directly. Example: to_csv({'total_cost': 2.0, 'by_agent': {'A': 2.0}, 'count': 2}) should return 'agent,cost\\nA,2.00\\nTOTAL,2.00\\n'.","criteria":"","idea":"idea_F","kind":"code","spec_commit":"d86e70cc9675845d295ea94c8f742ee80a221728","split":{"implement":0.6,"review":0.2,"spec":0.2},"task_id":"t4","title":"Export report to CSV: to_csv(summary) -> str"},"hash":"85b7aacd407e23fabca0980e9544659b8bab113df86cb73f72a0c3dd32f82772","prev_hash":"6cee2ab7ea5794fb47f010fcb7a12f5da4856490f822372bbf43ff7f7273a776","seq":42,"sig":null,"ts":"2026-07-17T00:01:02+00:00","type":"task_speced"}
